Genetic Risk Score¶

Date: 2021_03_22

Analyzed by: Sara Saez Atienzar

Background¶

Genetic risk score analysis can be used to identify shared genetic etiology between two different disease.

Goal¶

To Genetic risk scorePerform Mendelian randomization analysis to identify possible causal relationship between traits in ieu-a, ebi-a and ukb-a datasets and MG

Pipeline¶

Genetic risk score analysis uses the following sofwares/packages (and versions) R 4.0.3 plink 1.9 meta

MG plink files and covariate files:¶

  1. US: Imputed files: /data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/US/Imputation.USmerged.hg38/plinkForPRS/USmerged.UNRELATED.Imputed.pass.Rsq03MAF00001.chr*.bed/bim/fam Covariate file: /data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/US/COVARIATES.US_mg_noDups.UNRELATED.forImputed.txt Covariates to adjust for: GENDER,age_at_onset,PC1,PC2,PC4,PC5,PC6,PC8,PC9,PC10

  2. Italy: imputed files: /data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/Itals/Imputation.hg38/plinkForPRS/Itals.UNRELATED.Imputed.pass.Rsq03MAF00001.chr*.bed/bim/fam Covariate file: /data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/Itals/COVARIATES.Itals_mg_noDups.UNRELATED.forGLM.txt Covariates to adjust for: GENDER,age_at_onset,PC1,PC2,PC3,PC4,PC5,PC6,PC10

  3. Summary /data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/MetaAnalysis.hg38.ByCohort.rerun/USmerged.Itals.hg38/META_MG.USmerged.Itals.UNRELATED.hg38.Rsq03.glm_filteredDirection.HetISq80MAF001cases.rsid.txt

Analysis¶

Extract instruments¶

I will use the instrument of MR to calculate GRS. First, I extract the instruments of each significant trait

In [18]:
%%bash

cd /data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Data

module load R/4.0.3
R --vanilla --no-save

library(data.table)
library(TwoSampleMR)
#install.packages("MRinstruments")
library(MRInstruments)
#install.packages("WSpiller/RadialMR")
library("RadialMR") 
library("ieugwasr")
library("dplyr")
library("tidyverse")
sessionInfo()

# extract the instruments from SMR

#the token will be different each time, it needs to be prepare at the moment 
token <- "ya29.a0AfH6SMAYloNpa7fqlbyIgGtg6CMhB9iZ1dFEnj381EL59MlGla-OrK984t_wAhTaXtPCve5H5Am9yJydQxkNcfAkAowcqB1WZ5ETDjW06d6N9OJINbdkhqH2xEXJlxLAaU_PY4Pp7JavWeX23fKj8QEQ0FFqUw"

# choose the GWAS

##### ebiGCST005531

ebiGCST005531 = extract_instruments("ebi-a-GCST005531", p1 = 5e-08, clump = TRUE, p2 = 5e-08,
                                  r2 = 0.001, kb = 10000, access_token = token,
                                 force_server = TRUE)
ebiGCST005531
dim(ebiGCST005531)

MGtemp = fread("/data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/MetaAnalysis.hg38.ByCohort.rerun/USmerged.Itals.hg38/META_MG.USmerged.Itals.UNRELATED.hg38.Rsq03.glm_filteredDirection.HetISq80MAF001cases.rsid.txt", header = T)

head(MGtemp)
MGtemp$SNP = MGtemp$rsID
MGtemp$Freq1 = MGtemp$maf_EA.CASE
MGtemp$effect_allele = MGtemp$EffectAllele
MGtemp$other_allele = MGtemp$OtherAllele
MGtemp$Beta = MGtemp$beta
MGtemp$P.value = MGtemp$P

Out_data = format_data(MGtemp,type="outcome", beta_col = "Beta", se_col = "StdErr", eaf_col = "Freq1", pval_col = "P.value")
head(Out_data)
dat <- harmonise_data(exposure_dat=ebiGCST005531, outcome_dat=Out_data, action=2)
head(dat)
dim(dat)
data2 = select(dat, SNP, effect_allele.exposure, other_allele.exposure, beta.exposure)
write.table(data2,"ebiGCST005531_toscore.tab", quote = F, sep = " ", row.names=F)

##### ebiGCST002318

ebiGCST002318 = extract_instruments("ebi-a-GCST002318", p1 = 5e-08, clump = TRUE, p2 = 5e-08,
                                  r2 = 0.001, kb = 10000, access_token = token,
                                 force_server = TRUE)
ebiGCST002318
dim(ebiGCST002318)

%%bash 

cd /data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Data

module load R/4.0.3 
R --vanilla --no-save

# Load libraries
library(data.table)
library(tidyverse)
library(dplyr)
gwas = fread("/data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/MetaAnalysis.hg38.ByCohort.rerun/USmerged.Itals.hg38/META_MG.USmerged.Itals.UNRELATED.hg38.Rsq03.glm_filteredDirection.HetISq80MAF001cases.rsid.txt", header = T)
score = fread("/data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Data/ebiGCST005531_toscore.tab", header =T)
score$rsID = score$SNP


merged = merge(gwas, score, by ="rsID")
head(merged)

#genereta the variant name based on the position and allele
merged$chr = "chr"
merged$chrnm1 = paste(merged$chr, merged$CHROM, sep="")
merged$chrnm = paste(merged$chrnm1, merged$POS, sep = ":")
merged$A1 = paste(merged$effect_allele.exposure, merged$other_allele.exposure, sep =":")
merged$A2 = paste(merged$other_allele.exposure, merged$effect_allele.exposure, sep =":")
merged$marker1 = paste(merged$chrnm, merged$A1, sep = ":")
merged$marker2 = paste(merged$chrnm, merged$A2, sep = ":")
datafile1 = select(merged, marker1,effect_allele.exposure, beta.exposure)
datafile2 = select(merged, marker2,effect_allele.exposure, beta.exposure)
names(datafile2)[names(datafile2) == "marker2"] <- "marker1"
datafile <- rbind(datafile1,datafile2)
head(datafile)
print(datafile)

write.table(datafile,"ebiGCST005531_toscore.hg38.tab", quote = F, sep = " ", row.names = F)
write.table(datafile,"ebiGCST005531_toscore.hg38.noheader.tab", quote = F, sep = " ", col.names=F, row.names = F)

Calculate regression¶

In [5]:
%%bash

cd /data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Results/
module load R/4.0.3
R --vanilla --no-save

require(dplyr)
require(tidyverse)
require(ggplot2)
require(data.table)
require(RColorBrewer)

########UKB-a-77

profile = read.table("/data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Data/MG.USmerged.ukba77.profile", header = T)
dim(profile)
head(profile)
#PHENO FILE 
pheno = fread("/data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/US/COVARIATES.US_mg_noDups.UNRELATED.forImputed.txt", header = T)
dim(pheno)
head(pheno)


#merge pheno with profile
datatotal = merge(profile,pheno, by.x='FID',by.y='FID')
table(datatotal$diagnosis)


meanGRS <- mean(datatotal$SCORE)
sdGRS <- sd(datatotal$SCORE)
datatotal$SCOREZ <- (datatotal$SCORE - meanGRS)/sdGRS
head(datatotal)


p <- ggplot(datatotal, aes(x = as.factor(diagnosis), y=SCOREZ, fill=as.factor(diagnosis))) +
  geom_violin(alpha = 0.7, size = 1, colour = "gray30", trim=FALSE)
p2 <- p+geom_boxplot(width=0.4, fill="white", colour = "gray30") + 
  theme_classic(base_size = 15)

p3 = p2 + scale_fill_manual(values=c('#354E71','#4B878BFF')) + 
ylab("UKB-a-77 GRS risk (z-transformed)") + xlab("Diagnosis")



ggsave(filename = "/data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Plots/Violin.ukb77.US.png", width = 15, height = 15, dpi = 300, units = "cm", plot = p3)

#Regression risk versus disease status

datatotal$CASE <- datatotal$PHENO.y - 1
meanControls <- mean(datatotal$SCORE[datatotal$CASE == 0])
sdControls <- sd(datatotal$SCORE[datatotal$CASE == 0])
datatotal$zSCORE <- (datatotal$SCORE - meanControls)/sdControls	
grsTest <- glm(CASE ~ zSCORE + age_at_onset + GENDER + PC1 + PC2 + PC3 + PC4 + PC5 + PC6 + PC7 + PC8 + PC9 + PC10, family="binomial", data = datatotal)
beta <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Estimate"]
se <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Std. Error"]
p <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Pr(>|z|)"]
summary(grsTest)

outPut1 <- matrix(ncol = 5, nrow = length(2), NA)
colnames(outPut1) <- c("set","cohort","b","se","p")

outPut1[1] <- "ukb-a-77"
outPut1[2] <- "US"
outPut1[3] <- beta
outPut1[4] <- se
outPut1[5] <- p
head(outPut1)

outPut5 <- matrix(ncol = 5, nrow = length(2), NA)
colnames(outPut5) <- c("set","cohort","b","se","p")

outPut5[1] <- "ebiGCST002318"
outPut5[2] <- "US"
outPut5[3] <- beta
outPut5[4] <- se
outPut5[5] <- p
head(outPut5)


outputUS = rbind(outPut1, outPut2, outPut3, outPut4, outPut5)
head(outputUS)
write.table(outputUS, "GRS.US.risk.tab", quote = F, sep = "\t", row.names = F)
print(outputUS)

Itals = fread("GRS.Itals.risk.tab", header = T)
TOTAL = rbind(outputUS,Itals)
print(TOTAL)
write.table(TOTAL, "GRS.USplusItals.risk.tab", quote = F, sep = "\t", row.names = F)

%%bash

cd /data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Results/
module load R/4.0.3
R --vanilla --no-save

require(dplyr)
require(tidyverse)
require(ggplot2)
require(data.table)
require(RColorBrewer)

########ukb-a-77


profile = read.table("/data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Data/MG.Itals.ukba77.profile", header = T)
dim(profile)
head(profile)
#PHENO FILE 
pheno = fread("/data/NDRS_LNG/MyastheniaGravis/updated.April2020/Itals/COVARIATES.Itals_mg_noDups.UNRELATED.forGLM.txt", header = T)
dim(pheno)
head(pheno)


#merge pheno with profile
datatotal = merge(profile,pheno, by.x='FID',by.y='FID')
table(datatotal$diagnosis)

meanGRS <- mean(datatotal$SCORE)
sdGRS <- sd(datatotal$SCORE)
datatotal$SCOREZ <- (datatotal$SCORE - meanGRS)/sdGRS
head(datatotal)


p <- ggplot(datatotal, aes(x = as.factor(diagnosis), y=SCOREZ, fill=as.factor(diagnosis))) +
  geom_violin(alpha = 0.7, size = 1, colour = "gray30", trim=FALSE)
p2 <- p+geom_boxplot(width=0.4, fill="white", colour = "gray30") + 
  theme_classic(base_size = 15)

p3 = p2 + scale_fill_manual(values=c('#354E71','#4B878BFF')) + 
ylab("UKB-a-77 GRS risk (z-transformed)") + xlab("Diagnosis")



ggsave(filename = "/data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Plots/Violin.ukb77.Itals.png", width = 15, height = 15, dpi = 300, units = "cm", plot = p3)

#Regression risk versus disease status

datatotal$CASE <- datatotal$PHENO.y - 1
meanControls <- mean(datatotal$SCORE[datatotal$CASE == 0])
sdControls <- sd(datatotal$SCORE[datatotal$CASE == 0])
datatotal$zSCORE <- (datatotal$SCORE - meanControls)/sdControls	
grsTest <- glm(CASE ~ zSCORE + age_at_onset + GENDER + PC1 + PC2 + PC3 + PC4 + PC5 + PC6 + PC7 + PC8 + PC9 + PC10, family="binomial", data = datatotal)
beta <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Estimate"]
se <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Std. Error"]
p <- summary(grsTest)$coefficients["zSCORE","Pr(>|z|)"]
summary(grsTest)

outPut1 <- matrix(ncol = 5, nrow = length(2), NA)
colnames(outPut1) <- c("set","cohort","b","se","p")

outPut1[1] <- "ukb-a-77"
outPut1[2] <- "Italy"
outPut1[3] <- beta
outPut1[4] <- se
outPut1[5] <- p
head(outPut1)

%%bash

cd /data/ALS_50k/SaraSaez_ALS/2021-03-18.COLABORATION_MG/GRS/Results/

module load R/4.0.3
R --vanilla --no-save

require(dplyr)
require(tidyverse)
require(ggplot2)
require(data.table)
require(RColorBrewer)
library(metafor)
sessionInfo()


data <- fread("GRS.USplusItals.risk.tab", header = T)
head(data)
data$cohort = paste(data$set, data$cohort, sep = "_")

# Non-cancer illness code  self-reported: hypothyroidism/myxoedema || id:ukb-a-77
dat = filter(data, set =="ukb-a-77")
head(dat)

labs <- dat$cohort
yi   <- dat$b
sei  <- dat$se
resFe  <- rma(yi=yi, sei=sei, method="FE")
resRe  <- rma(yi=yi, sei=sei)

jpeg("randomEffectsForestPlot.ukb77.jpeg")
forest(resRe,  slab=labs, atransf=exp, xlab="Odds Ratio (95%CI)", mlab="Random Effects", col = "red", border = "red", cex=.75)
addpoly(resFe, atransf=exp, row=-1.5, mlab="Fixed Effects", col = "blue", border = "blue", cex=.75)
dev.off()

pdf("randomEffectsForestPlot.ukb77.pdf")
forest(resRe,  slab=labs, atransf=exp, xlab="Odds Ratio (95%CI)", mlab="Random Effects", col = "red", border = "red", cex=.75)
addpoly(resFe, atransf=exp, row=-1.5, mlab="Fixed Effects", col = "blue", border = "blue", cex=.75)
dev.off()

sink(file = "summary_fixedEffects_allCohorts.ukb77.txt")
summary(resFe)
sink()
resFe$pval
sink(file = "summary_randomEffects_allCohorts.ukb77.txt")
summary(resRe)
sink()
resRe$pval
